{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YYWLJVfYq87AWFcrbvqY5f","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16-8: Update All Tests for Verification Tier Rework\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: backlog\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a codeharness developer,\n     9→I want all tests to use the new `VerificationTier` vocabulary and cover the new functions,\n    10→So that `npm test` passes with zero regressions and the new tier system has full test coverage.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [ ] AC1: Given `verify-parser.test.ts`, when `classifyStrategy` tests are inspected, then they are replaced/supplemented with `classifyTier` tests covering all four tiers <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC2: Given `verify-parser.test.ts`, when `parseVerificationTag` tests are inspected, then they cover all four new tier names (`test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate`) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC3: Given `verify-parser.test.ts`, when backward compat tests are inspected, then `parseVerificationTag('<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->')` returns `'test-provable'` and `parseVerificationTag('<!-- verification: integration-required -->')` returns `'environment-provable'` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC4: Given new tests for `maxTier()`, when `maxTier(['test-provable', 'runtime-provable'])` is tested, then it returns `'runtime-provable'` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC5: Given new tests for `maxTier()`, when `maxTier([])` is tested, then it returns `'test-provable'` (default) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC6: Given new tests for `maxTier()`, when `maxTier(['test-provable', 'environment-provable', 'runtime-provable'])` is tested, then it returns `'environment-provable'` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC7: Given `verify.test.ts` (proof validation), when tier recognition tests are inspected, then they cover `**Tier:** test-provable`, `**Tier:** runtime-provable`, `**Tier:** environment-provable`, and `**Tier:** escalate` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC8: Given `verify.test.ts`, when backward compat tier test is inspected, then `**Tier:** unit-testable` still results in Docker enforcement being skipped <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC9: Given `validation-acs.test.ts`, when inspected, then any references to `getCliVerifiableACs()` are updated to `getTestProvableACs()` (or test both the new name and deprecated alias) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    23→- [ ] AC10: Given `validation-runner.test.ts`, when inspected, then any `verificationMethod` assertions still pass (no behavioral change, just comment updates in the source) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    24→- [ ] AC11: Given `parseStoryACs` tests, when a story file with new tier tags is parsed, then each `ParsedAC` has the correct `tier` field <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    25→- [ ] AC12: Given `npm test`, when run after all changes, then all tests pass with 0 failures <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    26→\n    27→## Technical Notes\n    28→\n    29→**Test files to update:**\n    30→\n    31→1. **`src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts`**\n    32→   - Add `describe('classifyTier')` block with tests for each tier's keywords\n    33→   - Update `describe('parseVerificationTag')` to test new tier names\n    34→   - Add backward compat tests for `parseVerificationTag` with old tag values\n    35→   - Update `describe('parseStoryACs')` to assert `tier` field on results\n    36→   - Keep existing `classifyStrategy` tests but they may need adjustment if the function signature changed\n    37→\n    38→2. **`src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify.test.ts`** (or `verify-blackbox.test.ts`)\n    39→   - Add/update tests for `validateProofQuality()` with all four `**Tier:**` values\n    40→   - Ensure `test-provable` and `runtime-provable` skip Docker enforcement\n    41→   - Ensure `environment-provable` requires Docker enforcement\n    42→   - Ensure `escalate` skips Docker enforcement\n    43→   - Keep `unit-testable` backward compat test\n    44→\n    45→3. **`src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-acs.test.ts`**\n    46→   - Update calls from `getCliVerifiableACs()` to `getTestProvableACs()`\n    47→   - Update calls from `getIntegrationRequiredACs()` to `getEnvironmentProvableACs()`\n    48→   - Or test both old (deprecated) and new function names\n    49→\n    50→4. **`src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-runner.test.ts`**\n    51→   - No behavioral changes expected — just verify tests still pass\n    52→\n    53→5. **New test file or section for `maxTier()` and `TIER_HIERARCHY`:**\n    54→   - Could go in `verify-parser.test.ts` or a new `tier-utils.test.ts`\n    55→   - Test `maxTier` with: empty array, single tier, multiple tiers, all four tiers\n    56→   - Test `TIER_HIERARCHY` ordering: index of `escalate` > index of `environment-provable` > index of `runtime-provable` > index of `test-provable`\n    57→   - Test `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` contains correct mappings\n    58→\n    59→6. **`src/modules/verify/__tests__/index.test.ts`**\n    60→   - May need updates if module re-exports changed\n    61→\n    62→## Files to Change\n    63→\n    64→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts` — Add `classifyTier` tests, update `parseVerificationTag` tests, add backward compat tests, assert `tier` field in `parseStoryACs` tests.\n    65→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify.test.ts` — Add proof validation tests for all four tier names.\n    66→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-blackbox.test.ts` — Update if black-box enforcement tests reference tier names.\n    67→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-acs.test.ts` — Update helper function names.\n    68→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-runner.test.ts` — Verify no regressions.\n    69→- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/index.test.ts` — Update if re-exports changed.\n    70→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YSsBTC1XS4UURKRwRVGfUv","session_id":"b3a82007-2654-437f-8d26-bde42ea858b0","uuid":"fe37784a-123b-403d-a232-c034ae6ddfd8","timestamp":"2026-03-27T13:48:04.892Z"}
