{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013WMycDzEvv9QkA53wtmvHS","type":"tool_result","content":"   380→- **MEDIUM: Missing test coverage for edge cases.** Empty string, unknown tags, and `unit-testable` backward compat had no test coverage. 3 new tests added.\n   381→- **LOW (not fixed): Broad keywords risk false-positive classification.** Keywords like \"function\", \"type\", \"export\" could match non-AC text. Deferred — acceptable for current use cases.\n   382→- **LOW (not fixed): Keyword overlap between dimensions.** Some keywords could plausibly match multiple tiers. Priority ordering (escalate > environment > runtime > test) mitigates this, but it is a known imprecision.\n   383→\n   384→### Category: Structural/process\n   385→\n   386→- **Epic 16 has no standard epics file.** Story definitions come from `tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md` instead of the usual epics document. The create-story subagent had to use the tech spec as authoritative source. This is a one-off deviation, but it means the standard story-creation workflow had to adapt.\n   387→\n   388→### Category: State management (recurring)\n   389→\n   390→- **3 stories stuck at \"review\" despite being done.** Stories 14-5, 14-6, and 16-1 had their git commits (marked done) but `sprint-state.json` was not updated. This is the same state sync issue flagged in sessions 1-3 — the state file drifts from reality when transitions happen outside the normal orchestrator flow.\n   391→\n   392→### Category: Redundant operations\n   393→\n   394→- **`npm test` run 3 times during verify phase.** The verify subagent ran the test suite three times when once with output capture (`tee`) would have sufficed. Wasted 2 Bash calls.\n   395→- **5 pre-existing test failures in unrelated modules.** The verify subagent had to reason about whether these were pre-existing or regressions. They were pre-existing, but diagnosing this cost tool calls.\n   396→\n   397→## 3. Cost Analysis\n   398→\n   399→### Session 4 delta (since Session 3 retro)\n   400→\n   401→| Metric | Session 3 (cumulative) | Session 4 (cumulative) | Delta |\n   402→|--------|------------------------|------------------------|-------|\n   403→| Total cost | $572.74 | $582.73 | **$9.99** |\n   404→| Total calls | 4,239 | 4,314 | **75** |\n   405→| Stories completed | 142 | 144 | **+2 (16-2 + state fixes count as work)** |\n   406→\n   407→Session 4 cost $9.99 across 75 API calls. The session handled story creation, code review, verification, and state cleanup for one story. At ~$10 for a full create-review-verify cycle, this is consistent with Session 3's $10.55 for a review-verify cycle.\n   408→\n   409→### Subagent-level token analysis (from session issues log)\n   410→\n   411→| Subagent Phase | Tool Calls | Breakdown | Files Read (unique/total) | Redundant Ops |\n   412→|----------------|-----------|-----------|--------------------------|---------------|\n   413→| create-story | 16 | Read:9, Grep:2, Glob:3, Bash:1, Write:1 | 10/10 | None |\n   414→| code-review | 18 | Bash:6, Read:9, Edit:6, Grep:2, Glob:4, Skill:1 | 9/10 | None |\n   415→| verify | 14 | Bash:8, Read:4, Grep:1, Write:1 | 5/5 | npm test x3 (2 redundant) |\n   416→\n   417→**Key observations:**\n   418→\n   419→- **create-story was Read-heavy (9/16 calls).** Expected — it needs to read the tech spec, existing parser code, and story templates. Zero redundant reads (10 unique out of 10 total).\n   420→- **code-review had balanced tool usage.** 6 Edits for 2 HIGH and 1 MEDIUM fix plus 3 new tests. No wasted calls. 9 unique files read out of 10 total (only 1 re-read).\n   421→- **verify had the only waste: triple test run.** 8 Bash calls, 3 of which were `npm test`. One run would have sufficed with output capture. This matches the duplicate-coverage-run pattern seen in Session 3.\n   422→- **Total redundant operations: 2 of 48 subagent calls (~4%).** Consistent with the ~5% waste rate observed in Session 2 and ~2% in Session 3.\n   423→- **No cross-phase file re-reading detected.** create-story, code-review, and verify each read their own set of files with minimal overlap. Good phase isolation.\n   424→\n   425→### Cumulative project costs\n   426→\n   427→| Metric | Value |\n   428→|--------|-------|\n   429→| Total API-equivalent cost | $582.73 |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TYUJxEN8SpXJAWBGfvsdeB","session_id":"b3a82007-2654-437f-8d26-bde42ea858b0","uuid":"25fd5cd6-1e27-4821-b58d-c4ce4daa2afc","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:10:06.650Z"}
