{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017C8ooy9fN1UnLXQKyjL5pH","type":"tool_result","content":"  1050→3. **Efficient tool usage.** 83 total tool calls for 12 ACs through 4 phases with only 3 redundant operations.\n  1051→4. **State corruption detected and fixed.** 16-5 and 16-6 were restored to correct `done` status, unblocking accurate sprint tracking.\n  1052→5. **Dev agent self-corrected naming ambiguity.** Caught \"unit-testable\" prose vs. tier name collision and fixed proactively without needing review feedback.\n  1053→6. **All 4015 tests passing, 0 regressions.** Build remained clean throughout.\n  1054→\n  1055→---\n  1056→\n  1057→## 5. What Went Wrong\n  1058→\n  1059→1. **State corruption recurrence.** sprint-state.json reverted 16-5 and 16-6 from `done` to `review` between sessions. Same root cause as session 1. Not yet fixed at the infrastructure level.\n  1060→2. **No Epic 16 epics file.** Every create-story phase wasted reads looking for a standard epics document before falling back to the tech spec. This has been flagged in 6 consecutive stories (16-2 through 16-7) without being addressed.\n  1061→3. **Pre-existing BATS failures still unfixed.** 6 BATS tests continue to fail across all sessions. These create noise in every dev and verify phase output.\n  1062→4. **Architecture concern left unresolved:** CODEHARNESS-PATCH template stamps Docker-oriented proof language on test-provable stories. The tier system is now in place but the templates have not been updated to reflect it.\n  1063→\n  1064→---\n  1065→\n  1066→## 6. Lessons Learned\n  1067→\n  1068→### Patterns to Repeat\n  1069→1. **Documentation-only stories are cheap and fast.** 16-7 was 83 tool calls for 12 ACs — roughly 40% of the cost of a typical code story. Batching doc updates into dedicated stories is efficient.\n  1070→2. **File-content ACs with grep verification** is a proven pattern for documentation stories. All 12 ACs verified via grep without needing build/test cycles.\n  1071→3. **Tail-bounded Bash outputs** (dev agent used `tail -80`, `tail -30`) prevent context blowup from test output.\n  1072→\n  1073→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1074→1. **Ignoring recurring state corruption.** Two incidents in one day. The ralph state reconciliation logic needs a fix, not just manual corrections.\n  1075→2. **Missing standard artifacts** (no epics file for Epic 16) creates repeated friction across every story in the epic. Better to create the artifact once upfront.\n  1076→3. **Leaving pre-existing test failures unfixed** adds noise to every session's dev and verify output.\n  1077→\n  1078→---\n  1079→\n  1080→## 7. Action Items\n  1081→\n  1082→| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n  1083→|---|--------|----------|-------|\n  1084→| 1 | Fix ralph state reconciliation to not overwrite `done` stories back to `review` | HIGH | Infrastructure |\n  1085→| 2 | Create Epic 16 epics file from tech spec to stop fallback behavior in create-story | MEDIUM | Process |\n  1086→| 3 | Fix 6 pre-existing BATS test failures (`all_tasks_complete`, `get_current_task`) | MEDIUM | Tech debt |\n  1087→| 4 | Update CODEHARNESS-PATCH template to be tier-aware (remove Docker language for test-provable stories) | MEDIUM | Story 16-8 or tech debt |\n  1088→| 5 | Complete Epic 16: story 16-8-update-all-tests is the only remaining story | HIGH | Next session |\n  1089→| 6 | Address `allFiles()` recreating array per call (LOW from code review) | LOW | Tech debt backlog |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TYUJxEN8SpXJAWBGfvsdeB","session_id":"b3a82007-2654-437f-8d26-bde42ea858b0","uuid":"5763f18c-d8a2-4c5f-82d3-3670879ed55c","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:10:13.059Z"}
